OL,3,CApril weather has been a 'month of two
OL,4,Chalves' Met Office says
OL,6,FGrey skies and rain mean April has
OL,7,Ffelt unusually cold, the Met Office
OL,8,Fsaid.
OL,10,FApril has been a "month of two
OL,11,Fhalves", with a warm fortnight
OL,12,Ffollowed by chillier weather ` meaning
OL,13,Fthat the average temperature for the
OL,14,Fmonth remains above the norm,
OL,15,Faccording to forecasters.
OL,17,FDespite this, a lack of sunshine and
OL,18,Fpersistent rain may have contributed
OL,19,Fto it feeling colder than expected for
OL,20,Fspringtime, the Met Office has
OL,21,Fsuggested.
