OL,3,CApril weather has been a 'month of two
OL,4,Chalves' Met Office says
OL,6,FForecasters expect warmer temperatures
OL,7,Fto return from Wednesday, with south
OL,8,Feast England set to enjoy highs of up
OL,9,Fto around 20C.
OL,11,FSo far this month, the maximum
OL,12,Ftemperature recorded was 21.8C in
OL,13,FWrittle, Essex, and a low of minus
OL,14,F6.3C in Shap, Cumbria ` with a UK-wide
OL,15,Faverage of 8.4C, according to the Met
OL,16,FOffice.
OL,18,FData from the forecaster shows that
OL,19,Fthe UK has seen an average of 99mm of
OL,20,Frainfall in April so far, which is 27%
OL,21,Fhigher than usual for the month.
