OL,3,CApril weather has been a 'month of two
OL,4,Chalves' Met Office says
OL,6,FAmy Bokota, senior meteorologist at
OL,7,Fthe Met Office, said: "It's been a
OL,8,Fmonth of two halves where it's been
OL,9,Fquite warm for the first half, and
OL,10,Fthen quite cool up until now, and then
OL,11,Fit's expecting to warm back up again.
OL,13,F"So on the whole, it'll probably be on
OL,14,Fthe warmer side of average.
OL,16,F"It's definitely wetter than average
OL,17,Ffor the UK as a whole, so there you're
OL,18,Fgoing to be seeing rain and grey skies
OL,19,Fand a lot of places have been quite
OL,20,Fdull so far for the time of year."
